<item>
            <title>[FLINK-19900] Wrong property name for surefire log4j configuration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-19900</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Log4j uses &lt;tt&gt;log4j.configurationFile&lt;/tt&gt; system property for passing a configuration file. In our surefire configuration we use &lt;tt&gt;log4j.configuration&lt;/tt&gt; property instead which has no effect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;plugin&amp;gt;
	&amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&amp;lt;/groupId&amp;gt;
	&amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;maven-surefire-plugin&amp;lt;/artifactId&amp;gt;
	&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;2.22.1&amp;lt;/version&amp;gt;
	&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;
         ....
		&amp;lt;systemPropertyVariables&amp;gt;
                ....
			&amp;lt;log4j.configuration&amp;gt;${log4j.configuration}&amp;lt;/log4j.configuration&amp;gt;
		&amp;lt;/systemPropertyVariables&amp;gt;
                ....
         &amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
